TOURETTE DISORDER - USA: (NEW YORK) OUTBREAK
********************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 28 Nov 2011
Source: DemocratandChronicle.com [edited]
http://www.democratandchronicle.com/article/20111128/NEWS01/111128016


After an in-depth investigation by the New York State Health
Department as well as school officials, Le Roy School District
Superintendent Kim Cox says they still have no answers regarding an
unusual outbreak of Tourette-like symptoms in a group of 6 students at
the Junior-Senior High School.

Last month [October 2011] health officials began looking into medical
records, environmental conditions, and other factors after the
students began exhibiting neurological tics, similar to Tourette's
syndrome. Health Department spokesman Peter Constantakes told WGRZ-TV
this morning [28 Nov 2011] that they did conclude that other students
and staff are not at risk and there have been no other cases
reported.

While a cause has not been found, they are confident that the
conditions and symptoms the students are exhibiting are real and not a
figment of imagination or power of suggestion. Constantakes says this
type of outbreak is extremely unusual, and they were not able to find
another like it. In cases that showed similarities, stress factors
seemed to play a role in the patient's symptoms.

The Le Roy School District issued a statement to parents and residents
over the holiday week [Thanksgiving, 24 Nov 2011] explaining the
situation and reaffirming that the health, safety, and well being of
students and school staff is their top priority. Cox said that the
district would provide no further comment on the issue.

[Byline: Pete Gallivant]

